## 9. RLS (Row Level Security)

Chaque user voit et modifie **uniquement ses items**. Pas d'exception.

```sql
-- SELECT
create policy "wishlist_select_own"
  on wishlist_items for select
  to authenticated
  using (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- INSERT
create policy "wishlist_insert_own"
  on wishlist_items for insert
  to authenticated
  with check (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- DELETE
create policy "wishlist_delete_own"
  on wishlist_items for delete
  to authenticated
  using (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- UPDATE (optionnel, rare sur wishlist)
-- create policy "wishlist_update_own" ...
```

Mêmes policies pour `compare_items`. Anon role = AUCUN accès — les guests ne touchent que leur localStorage.

**À tester** : ouvrir deux sessions en parallèle (user A + user B), vérifier qu'aucun leak cross-user.

